{"title": "Exponential Potential", "content": "Ah, you just opened up your newest game and have been Easing into the Adventure. Maybe there's some Elemental Rock\u0096Paper\u0096Scissors, or Standard Status Effects, but you can handle that. Then you get a new spell!\n\nA few levels later, you are the Squishy Wizard equivalent of MacGyver and have a spell for every situation, effect or possibility. Or a weapon, or a tool, or a shiny rock made from lifeforce. One of the reasons for Linear Warriors, Quadratic Wizards.\n\nCousin to Crippling Overspecialization, in a nutshell this trope refers to any video game or possibly other setting where as you level up, your pool of actions and spells increases more and more, until you have a spell for literally everything and lose sight of the actual good choices, or are simply screwed over by the AI enemies using obscure or unexpected ones. Most common in games that allow you to create your own spells, whether by scribbling runes in a different order or by making your own.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ExponentialPotential", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MacGyver", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LostMagic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/KamenRider", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderDecade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderDouble", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderOOO", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderFourze", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderGhost", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderBuild", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/GeniusTheTransgression", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/MageTheAscension", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/MagicTheGathering", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheElderScrolls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsIIIMorrowind", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsIVOblivion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsVSkyrim", "/